cc:Work.dc:title: ASL alphabet handshapes
cc:Work.dc:description: American Sign Language handshapes for all 26 characters in the Latin alphabet, and all 10 Arabic digits.

cc:Agent.dc:title:
A freeware but nonfree font was used to create a public domain chart by Wikipedia user Ds13, which was annotated by Wikipedia user Dancor, and then converted to SVG by Wikipedia user Marnanel (Thomas Thurman).
The original font used was Galludet-TT, copyright (c) 1991 by David Rakowski, available from ftp://ylcftp.uoregon.edu/fonts/asl/gal.zip.
